<subsection xml:id="subsec-bearings">
    <title>Bearings</title>
    <definition xml:id="def-bearing">
        <statement>
            <p>
                <term>Bearing</term> is the <em>angle</em> in degrees measured in the <em>clockwise direction</em> from north. 
            </p>
            <p>
                <term>Bearing</term> is also known as <term>true bearing</term>.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </definition>
    <activity>
        <p>
            <m>\textbf{Work in groups}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol marker="1. ">
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Click and drag point <m>A</m> or point <m>B</m> to different positions on the coordinate plane.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Observe how the <em>Bearing of B from A</em> and <em>Bearing of A from B</em> change dynamically.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Record at least five different sets of bearings shown as you move the points.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Try to determine a pattern or relationship between the two bearings.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        What did you notice about the two bearings? Share your observations with a classmate or in a small group.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        How can you find the bearing of A from B if you know the bearing of B from A?
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </activity>
    <figure>
        <caption></caption>
        <interactive xml:id="geogebra-bearings-activity" platform="geogebra" width="110%" aspect="1:1">
            <slate xml:id="bearings-activity" surface="geogebra" material="qpmdhdp8" aspect="1:1" />
        </interactive>
    </figure>
    <p>
        <m>\textbf{Key Takeaway}</m>
    </p>
    <remark>
        <p>
            <ol marker="a)">
                <li>
                    <p>
                        if the bearing of B from A is <m>073^\circ</m>, then the bearing of A from B is <m>073^\circ + 180^\circ = 253^\circ</m>.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        If the bearing of B from A is <m>195^\circ</m>, then the bearing of A from B is <m>195^\circ - 180^\circ = 15^\circ</m>.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </remark>
